<Author>KATZLondon
<Content>Reasonable Good location, great transport links, breakfast ok (not great for fried but ok for continental) beds VERY comfortable. However the rooms have no air conditioning which means you will probably not be able to sleep without the windows open during the summer as it gets stifling hot. The only problem is that if you have a room at the front the traffic is VERY noisy so bring earplugs. The hotel is likely to be fully booked so they will be unable to change rooms. One of our party had to change rooms as it smelled of cigarette smoke but they changed it. They also tried to give us a twin room when we had paid for a double but we insisted they changed it. (These were all front-facing rooms) There is a cool little place that looks like a coffee shop next door that does huge cocktails for 5 euro. We found a lovely Italian half way down Leibniz Str and more restaurants around Walter- Benjamin Platz 
