<Author>jeffcar
<Content>Great Location Stayed for three nights at the Kant with my wife, we were worried about airport transfer from Schoenfeld Airport , could not be easier took the S9 stright to Charlottenburg station . then 3 minute walk to Hotel .Make sure you get a welcome travel card at the station excellent value .We did not arrive until 10.30 pm so we asked reception to recommend a nearby Restaurant , the Italian across the road was excellent value and staff very friendly .The hotel we found very clean , the Breakfast was very good also, the drinks in the bar are a bit expensive ,look for the bar next door though a lot cheaper .Right outside the hotel is the bus stop you can get one of two buses from here to the zoological station area , very easy the last one returns at 1.30pm, but you can also catch the S9 again from the zoological stationgood night out is at the Irish bar in the europa centre live music until 3.00amAll in all we found Berlin and the Kant a good experience and will return soon 
