<Author>Catherine.Murphy
<Content>Liked the Kant Very convenient. Enjoyed staying in this part of Berlin. Great shops, restaurants play facilities. Fabulous transport links. Everything cheap and good quality.We had a problem with our room on the first night. It was too small, and overlooked main road. Moved on the second day to a larger room, refurbished and overlooking the courtyard. Peaceful. Enjoyed breakfast.All in all, a great week's stay would go back.The brochure did say complementary coffeee available 24/7 - not the case except at breakfast.Staff knowledgeable and helpful except when sending us to the long closed Egyptology museum.Looking forward to going back to Berlin and the Kant soon. 
